      • countDigit

        public static int countDigit​(int n,
                             int d)
        Parameters:
        n -
        d - : digit to count, d is between 0 and 9 (inclusive on both sides)
        Returns:
        the number of times digit d exists in integer n IMPORTANT countDigit(0, d) for any d should return 0 countDigit(10074, 0) = 2 countDigit(38, 8) = 1 countDigit(888, 8) = 3 countDigit(12345, 6) = 0 countDigit(0, 0) = 0 (NOT 1)
